Objectives / Learning Outcome(s) / Major:
1.	EXPLAIN THE UNDERLYING CONCEPTS IN FINANCIAL REPORTING;
2.	IDENTIFY, EXPLAIN, AND IMPLEMENT THE BASIC STEPS IN THE ACCOUNTING CYCLE;
3.	DESCRIBE THE SPECIFIC ELEMENTS OF THE BALANCE SHEET; 
4.	EXPLAIN THE PURPOSE OF AN INCOME STATEMENT AND DEFINE ITS ELEMENTS;
5.	DEFINE AND IDENTIFY DIFFERENT TYPES OF RECEIVABLES;
6.	DETERMINE THE EXPENDITURES INCLUDED IN THE COST OF INVENTORY AND THE FLOW OF COSTS;
7.	IDENTIFY THE COSTS TO BE INCLUDED IN THE ACQUISITION OF PROPERTY, PLANT, AND EQUIPMENT;
8.	EXPLAIN THE ISSUED INVOLVED IN SELECTING DEPRECIATION METHODS AND THEIR DISCLOSURE;
9.	ACCOUNT FOR INVESTMENTS IN DEBT AND EQUITY SECURITIES;
10.	EXPLAIN THE GAAP FOR PENSION PLANS, INCLUDING COMPUTING PENSION EXPENSE AND RECOGNIZING PENSION LIABILITIES AND ASSETS; AND
11.	DEMONSTRATE AN UNDERSTANDING ON THE DEFINITION OF A LEASE AND HOW TO ACCOUNT FOR AND CLASSIFY THEM.
